OL,3,CRoman altars acquired for nation to go
OL,4,Con show for first time
OL,6,FExperts described the cult of Mithras
OL,7,Fas a secretive, male-only religion
OL,8,Fwhich celebrated the triumph of good
OL,9,Fover evil and light over darkness.
OL,11,FThe altars were excavated at Inveresk
OL,12,Fin East Lothian and date to around
OL,13,F140AD ` when southern Scotland was
OL,14,Freoccupied under Antoninus Pius.
OL,16,FCurators said the altars help reveal
OL,17,Fnew details about the beliefs and
OL,18,Flives of soldiers on the frontier.
