OL,3,CRoman altars acquired for nation to go
OL,4,Con show for first time
OL,6,FThe other altar honours Mithras
OL,7,Fhimself and is decorated with carvings
OL,8,Flinked to the god Apollo, another god
OL,9,Fof light, including a lyre, a griffin
OL,10,Fand a plectrum as well as two ravens,
OL,11,Fwhich are often seen in Mithraic
OL,12,Fimagery.
OL,14,FBoth altars were dedicated by a
OL,15,Flegionary centurion thought to be
OL,16,FGaius Cassius Flavianus whose name was
OL,17,Fabbreviated on the altar as G CAS FLA.
OL,19,FIt is thought he was probably in
OL,20,Fcommand of the fort garrison at the
OL,21,Ftime.
